\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection
Game End
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The Game concludes when the blood bank has no more blood in it for the first
 time.
 The additional pts set aside at the start of the game are then added, so
 the remainder of the set of Operating Rounds can continue.
 At the start of the next Stock Round, the game is over.
 If the bank is exhausted during a Stock Round, the game continues until
 the end of the next set of Operating Rounds.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The winner is the player whose value is the highest.
 The value is their total blood holdings, plus the value of all their shares
 multiplied by the current price for those shares.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The game may also be concluded immediately if a player goes bankrupt.
 After all, the time has come where Dracula will feast.
 
\end_layout

