 amount of operational rounds until after the following stock round.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection
Operating order
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Firstly, any still open associates (other than Lupin's Lipids and Blundell
 Transfusions) pay their revenue to their owners (being, a front, or a player).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Next, if still open, Lupin's Lipids runs.
 It uses the same rules as running a regular front, except it has no additional
 offices, can not buy monsters, and always pays half of its dividend to
 its owner, and half to its treasury.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Next, if still open, Blundell Transfusions runs.
 It uses the same rules as running a regular front, except the only monster
 it can buy is 'Nurses', and always pays half of its dividend to its owner,
 and half to its treasury.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Following this, all of the other fronts have their operating round.
 They operate once during the operating round in order from the highest
 stock value to the lowest.
 If there are multiple fronts on the same space, then they operate with
 the top front in the space going first, and then the next down and so on.
 If the price is the same, but they are in different spaces, the right-most
 company goes first.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
As such, when moving stock tokens on the stock market, always move stock
 tokens at the bottom, underneath any tokens in the same space.
\end_layout

