\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
A front that has any legal route must own a monster by the end of the Buy
 Monsters phase.
 If it does not have a monster, and does not have enough blood to purchase
 a monster from the bank, the president must contribute blood until the
 front has sufficient blood to purchase a monster.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection
Presidential contributions
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Presidential contributions are only permitted if the company is forced to
 purchase a monster, and does not have enough blood to purchase a monster
 from the bank.
 Any available, legal monster from the bank may be purchased from the bank
 with a presidential contribution; it does not need to be the cheapest available
 monster in the bank.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
A president must first contribute from their own treasury.
 If their treasury has insufficient blood, they must sell shares (using
 the ordinary rules, including limits in the market, and stock movement)
 until they have sufficient blood to contribute.
 Once the player has sufficient blood to contribute to the front to purchase
 the monster, it may not sell any more shares.
 The president decides which shares to sell, and in which order.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The sales may not change the presidency of the front which the president
 is contributing to.
 The sales may change the presidency of other fronts.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Paragraph*
Bankruptcy
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
If a player can not sell sufficient shares to allow a monster to be purchased,
 the player is bankrupted, ending the game.
 The player must sell as many shares as they are able before declaring bankruptc
y.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Paragraph*
Technical bankruptcy
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
If:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
a player has presidency of more than one front;
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
a players fronts have exactly one permanent monster between them;
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
the sum of the players fronts treasuries and the player's treasury is less
 than the cheapest monster available;
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
the player would otherwise be bankrupt; and
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
the front has either 0 pts of blood or no other front is willing to sell
 a permanent monster for the full treasury of the front;
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
then they must declare a technical bankruptcy, ending the game.
 The player then treats it as a bankruptcy.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection
Purchase Associates
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
A front may purchase an associate off a player for any price from 1 pt to
 twice the base cost of the associate, with the consent of the player who
 owns the associate and the president of the front.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Unlike the other parts of the OR, this may be done at any time during the
 front's OR, including after the purchase of monsters before the next front
