\begin_layout Subsection
Associates
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Associates serve the purpose of private companies in 1830.
 They are people and organisations under the thumb of Dracula's children
 who can provide some special service, pay protection money to the players
 (in the form of anonymous blood donations, ‘honestly’ retrieved) and be
 sold to the fronts to extract some of the blood out of them with a legitimate
 air.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
All associates are listed in the reference section of this manual.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection
Associate auction
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The associate auction is at the start of the game.
 It is an 1830-style 'waterfall' auction.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The player who makes the first bid is the one who has most recently had
 blood taken.
 Failing that, the player who most recently watched a horror film.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Starting with the first player, going clockwise, the current player may:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Pass
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Purchase the lowest priced unsold associate at face value 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Put a multiple-of-five bid on one of the associates that is higher than
 its purchase price, and any current bids.
 Any bids (even if not winning) on an unsold associate are put aside and
 can not be used until that associate is sold by purchase or auction.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
A pass does not stop the player from continuing to take part in the auction.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
When the lowest price associate is purchased or auctioned, then:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
If there's no bids on the next associate, continue the associate auction
 with the next player after the one who purchased the last share.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
If there’s only one bidder on the next associate, it is purchased by that
 bidder
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
If there’s multiple bidders on the next associate, it is auctioned off.
 Starting with player to the left of current highest bid, bidders on that
 associate who are not winning the auction may make a multiple-of-five bid
 higher than the current price.
 A player who passes during an auction for a specific associate may not
 reenter bid again for that associate.
 Only people who bid on the associate before it was auctioned off participate
 in that auction.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
After this purchase or auction, if the new lowest-priced unsold associate
 has one or more bids on it, repeat this process again until either all
 companies are sold or the new lowest-priced unsold associate has no bids.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
When an associate is bought by purchase or auction, the player pays its
 purchase price, or their bid, to the bank.
 If the associate has other bids, those players get that money back; it
 is no longer reserved.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
If all players pass without everything being sold, then the price of the
 current associate is reduced by 5 pts, the round continues, and each associate
 that has been purchased pays their revenue to its owner.
 Those associates that run as fronts have an operating round in the order
 of Lupin’s Lipids followed by Blundell Transfusions.
 In the unlikely event that an associate is reduced to 0 pts, a player must
 not pass and must purchase it for free.
\end_layout

